title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message: Macbook came in as dead, did a physical inspection on the board, found a hairline crack on the u5200, replaced it. No PPBUS short. Board is not drawing 20V. Your input will be highly appreciated.

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message: This is a surprise, pls, enlighten me, how can a board that is only able to draw 5V have 12V on it??

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
Since 2015/6, MacBook boards have buck-boost converter on input.
Didn't think why there are 2 MOSFET pairs (Q5230/40, before and after L5230)?

3V8_AON present?
Check some PMU LDOs.

Did you try DFU?

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
3V8_AON is present 
Pls can you specify the PMU and LDOs
It didn't enter DFU
But I did check some coils at the U8100
L8100 that should be 1.06V was 0.7V
L8110 no voltage present
L8280 that should be 0.94V has 0.7V
All other coils voltage are present

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
Be sure to check ALWAYS voltage on the output pin of the coils; where the filter cap is placed.

PMU LDOs on page 28 & 33.

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
L7800 MUST have 3.8V on pin 2; comes from 3V8_AON.
If you get 5V at C7800, is OK.

Check for short on all big coils.
Also check at small coils near U7700 and U8100; especially the ones without voltage pulse.

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
L7800/2 is connected to C7800/1 and it has 5V on it. L7800/1 has 3.8V on it.
I've checked all coils around U7700 and U8100, they are not shorted.

title: 820-02020 not drawing 20V stuck at 5v
message:
Do you still have pulsing L82xx coils?
You've said 0.7V on L8280 before; supposedly not pulsing.

BTW, always check DC voltage on the coils output pin, where the filter caps are placed.
